Package: sbyops
Type: Package
Title: Fast Tabular Column Selection Operations
Version: 0.5.1
Authors@R: person("Joao B. G.", "de Brito", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "joaobatista.goncalvesdebrito@ugent.be")
Description: Accelerates tabular data preprocessing through high-performance,
    pipe-friendly column selection routines. As a core component of the
    'sabby' ecosystem, it integrates an intuitive R interface with deeply
    optimized Fortran and C++ backends. Built for heavy analytical
    workloads, the package features native OpenMP parallelism and direct
    linkage to Intel oneMKL and standard BLAS/LAPACK libraries, engineered
    to support aggressive GCC and Intel compiler optimizations. Initial
    capabilities include ultra-fast dimensionality reduction via modal
    frequency and Pearson correlation.
